HEADWORD: Pulmonata
<hw>Pul`mo*na"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
from L. <ets>pulmo</ets>, <ets>-onis</ets>, a lung.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An extensive division, or sub-class, of
hermaphrodite gastropods, in which the mantle cavity is modified into an
air-breathing organ, as in Helix, or land snails, Limax, or garden
slugs, and many pond snails, as Limn⟦ae⟧a and Planorbis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pulmonate</ent>⟦br⟧
